The Division Director may approve a voluntary supervisory stock conversion only if:
The Division Director determines that:
The Division Director would have grounds to seek the appointment of a conservator or receiver under this title;
No equity value would be realized by the savings and loan association's mutual account holders after liquidation of the association;
Severe financial conditions exist that threaten the financial stability of the savings and loan association;
The conversion to a capital stock form is likely to improve the financial condition of the savings and loan association;
The association will be viable after the conversion; and
The approval of the conversion is not detrimental to the public interest; and
The approval imposes the same conditions that federal law requires or permits.

A conversion under this section is not subject to the requirements contained in the following sections of this title:
§§ 9-206 through 9-208, inclusive;
§§ 9-216 through 9-222, inclusive;
§§ 9-601 through 9-609, inclusive; and
§§ 9-627 through 9-630, inclusive.
